    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-08-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-08-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="696"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d696">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/6451</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        French Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_JJJ1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jusserand</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1923</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 17, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                    receipt of your note of the 11th instant regarding a report received by your
                    Government from its Consul at Monrovia to the effect that the Liberian
                    Government has expressed a wish that the German Consul, the German Receiver, and
                    the German women and children be put as early as possible on an English or
                    Spanish steamer bound for England, whence they would proceed to Germany by way
                    of a Scandinavian country, and to say in reply that this Government would have
                    no objection to this, if it is the wish of the Liberian Government, but that the
                    Department has received no advice in that relation from the American Minister at
                    Monrovia.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
